==English==
===Noun===
'''Beigist'''

# Sell out; conformist. Beigeist as in the color beige, as in ‘beigeocracy’, that being the color of Starbucks lattes and corporate conformity. It is a term coined by writer [http://en.wikipedia.com/wiki/Mark_Ames Mark Ames] and popularized in Ames' [http://www.nypress.com/16/35/news&columns/feature.cfm notorious attack on writer Chuck Klosterman], to describe anyone of Manhattan LA media ilk or other forces of bourgeois/corporate mediocracy or conformity.

[http://www.gawker.com/news/diary/beigeism-013153.php According to Gawker], Beigeist is "hipster slang used to slap those who march in lockstep with “beige” corporate America. Starbucks is mentioned often, perhaps because lattes are beige, as are Gap Chinos.